{
  "page_type": "function",
  "name": "GNSSGetCurLon",
  "category": "J1939",
  "title": "GNSSGetCurLon",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/J1939/GNSSNodeLayer/Functions/CAPLfunctionGNSSgetcurlon.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "double GNSSGetCurLon();"
  ],
  "description": [
    "The function returns the current longitude at which the receiver is located. If a value of 0.0 is returned, the GNSSGetLastError function must be used to check whether the value is valid (see error codes)."
  ],
  "parameters": [],
  "return": "current longitude (in degrees)",
  "example": {
    "description": [],
    "code": "double lon;\nlon = GNSSGetCurLon();\n\nif (lon == 0 && GNSSGetLastError() != 0 ) {\n  write(“Error: Invalid current longitude”);\n}"
  },
